rComments: Don't take if you don't have to. This teacher doesn't give enough time to complete impossible quizzes and will not listen to students concerns or care about anything.
no sympathy to students, weekly quiz 30 questions but only 15 minutes time and some of them were never been mentioned in lecture or readings
Great prof. Take eco6122 with him instead of the others, you won't regret it!

He is a very kind person but lacks the ability to actually teach. I found that I had learnt next to nothing from him but more from teaching myself. He is all over the place and very unorganized. I personally would not recommend the class to anyone.

Prof Simons was fairly kind. He didn't hold live lectures, but instead posted recorded lectures a week in advance. There wasn't much testing, just weekly quizzes and 2 assignments. The quizzes had everything on his lectures and slideshows so PAY ATTENTION!

First comment for him, he literally skipped some of the more complicate questions that being asked by the students during the tutoirial session, and posted some messy hand written notes a day after, which still doesn't help much , cuz thoese questions were still not answered.

The class is aboriginal economics. Consists of 5 large lectures for the first half and presentations for the second half. The prof is actually terrible but really easy marker. Tends to rant. Unable to let people present fully - he keeps interrupting then rushes students to finish and skip parts of their PPT because of his time-wasting.

I'm taking special topics 3 with him right now. Very clear criteria, super easy quizzes, fantastic lectures, and great conversations. Just show up and do the work to pass - very easy course and you actually learn quite a bit. Great lectures.

Ooen Book Quizzes (doesnt believe in making students memorize equations). Posts lots of past quizzes, past exams, and all lecture slides on brightspace. Class average for the first assignment qorth 15% was 90%. Posted the answere for half of the third assignment to help students out. Dude's a gem. Made course so much easier than it couldve been

Aboriginal economics course was really good. Im not an economist but I liked the course very much. The best course I ever took. Not so hard, quizzes questions are given in advance. You can learn the answers from notes. So to get the full mark is easy. Assignments are not difficult either. Essays and presentation was fun. A lot of discussions.

Best course of my undergrad. I am a non-ECO student who took his special topic course on aboriginal economics. He is hilarious and makes the course very interesting and not too challenging. You need to put in some work to do well on quizzes and assignments but nothing unreasonable. The ritual he performed during the last class was unforgettable.

I honestly don't understand why this prof has been rated so highly.. The lectures were boring, he didn't do enough examples in class to show us how to apply the material, and his tests (including his quizzes) were really though. The textbook was also useless. The assignments are the only okay part. I don't recommend taking his class.
best ever! must take his course, you will get an A
Very decent lecturer. Some assignments are hard. Overall, very useful class. Maybe a bit easy for a 3rd level course.
I also expected A+, but got A. But I like the course and the prof is very helpful. He even organized a reading/help group for weak students. Still the course could be more challenging.
Well, I was expecting A, but I've got A-. Still the course was good and the lecturer is great.

He organized supplementary hours for weak students and pay a lot of attention to them. maybe too much. His exams are OK and his grading system is nice: you have to submit only 2 out of 3 home works and do 1 out of 2 midterms. Assignments are very good. I learned a lot.
Good lecturer. More attention to homeworks.

His tests ok but his lectures are BORING.. never, i repeat, NEVER take a 3 hour lecture with him.. i have two 80 minute lectures with him however i'm never able to focus for more than 10 minutes with him.
He is very helpful.
